results.occurrenceRemarks: Difficult photo, but classic booby shape is evident.  It was originally seen at close range just offshore from the beach but after retrieving my camera it had drifted farther out.  It was completely dark brown above with a fully brown upper breast down to below the water line, a horn-colored bill and clean white undersides, as evidenced by the white undertail as it loafed on the water's surface.

results.occurrenceRemarks: Three birds were seen perched on one of the large electrical transmission towers crossing the water. One was an adult. The other two were immature birds.   One or two birds had been reported earlier to Texbirds, but I think our sighting of three was the first time that many birds were reported. A day or so later, someone saw four birds.  Other observers with me: Laurie Foss and Byron Stone. Photo (digiscoped from a great distance) compliments of Laurie Foss.
